    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Arc
    Abstract class representing an Arc in a Petri net, connecting a Place to a Transition.
    ArcAdapter
    Adapter class for the `Arc` element in the PetriNet implementation.
    ConsoleTest
    Unit test class for testing console output and duplicate arc detection in a Petri net.
    EmArc
    EmArc (Empty Arc) class extending ExArc.
    EnArc
    EnArc (Entering Arc) class extending Arc.
    ExArc
    ExArc (Exiting Arc) class extending Arc.
    InteractiveMain
    Interactive main class to demonstrate the functionality of the Petri Net with user input.
    IPetriNet
    Interface IPetriNet defines the core methods for managing and executing a PetriNet model.
    Main
    Main class to demonstrate the functionality of the Petri net.
    PetriNet
    PetriNet class implementing the IPetriNet interface.
    PetriNetAdapter
    Adapter class to link the `PetriNetInterface` from PNEditor with the `PetriNet` class from the custom PetriNet implementation.
    Place
    Represents a place in a PetriNet, which holds a certain number of tokens and manages incoming and outgoing arcs.
    PlaceAdapter
    Adapter class for integrating the `Place` class from the custom Petri Net implementation with the PNEditor framework's `AbstractPlace`.
    Transition
    Transition class representing a transition in the Petri net.
    TransitionAdapter
    Adapter class for integrating the `Transition` class from the custom PetriNet implementation with the PNEditor's `AbstractTransition`.
    ZArc
    ZArc class extending ExArc.
